16 Barrios Mead, which welcomed 17 young students for two weeks of inspiring learning and
17 community connection; and
18 WHEREAS, under her leadership, Los Niños Primero has grown to impact more than 6,200
19 Latino children, youth, and families through programs that foster academic readiness,
20 community engagement, and leadership development; and
21 WHEREAS, Maritza Morelli has been widely recognized for her exemplary efforts,
22 receiving the Congressional Honor from Congresswoman Lucy McBath in 2022 and being
23 named one of Georgia's 50 Most Influential Latino Leaders by the Georgia Hispanic
24 Chamber of Commerce; and
25 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
26 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body congratulate and commend Maritza Morelli for receiving the 2025
29 Yellow Rose Nikki T. Randall Servant Leadership Award and extend best wishes for her
30 continued success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
33 Maritza Morelli.
